  <title>SCIAF : The Kulima Programme</title>
  <description>This project will focus on addressing falling levels of food production in Zambia which have resulted from severely degraded soils and the impact of climate change to establish sustainable agricultural practices. The project will work with 1,350 small-holder farmers to sustainably increase food production levels through the adoption of organic and conservation farming techniques to improve the fertility and resilience to climate change of their soils. SCIAF will also work with the James Hutton Institute to promote the benefits of sustainable agricultural systems for small scale farmers to the Zambian Government. South to South learning will be promoted with Malawi and Burundi through exchange visits.</description>
